    "25029775": {
      "title": "The quality of life of medical students studying in New Zealand: a comparison with nonmedical students and a general population reference group",
      "abstract": "Background: Quality of life is an essential component of learning and has strong links with the practice and study of medicine. There is burgeoning evidence in the research literature to suggest that medical students are experiencing health-related problems such as anxiety, depression, and burnout. Purpose: The aim of the study was to investigate medical students’ perceptions concerning their quality of life. Methods: Two hundred seventy-four medical students studying in their early clinical years (response rate = 80%) participated in the present study. Medical students were asked to fill in the abbreviated version of the World Health Organization Quality of Life questionnaire to elicit information about their quality of life perceptions in relation to their physical health, psychological health, social relationships, and environment. Subsequently, their responses were compared with two nonmedical students groups studying at a different university in the same city and an Australian general population norm..."
    }
